The paper discusses the design of a hybrid control system for a robot, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The use of memristor-based non-linearity suggests a focus on neural networks and neuromorphic computing, which are subfields of machine learning (cs.NE). The ant-inspired algorithms for information transfer protocols suggest a focus on swarm intelligence and distributed systems, which are subfields of control systems (cs.SY) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the use of approximations and quick decision-making suggests a focus on optimization and decision-making, which are subfields of machine learning (cs.LG).
